title: China donates 24 tons of food and anti-epidemic supplies to Mauritania for Ramadan May 2020
description: On May 10, 2020, 32 Chinese-funded enterprises and institutions donated 24 tons of food materials and anti-epidemic supplies to Mauritania for Ramadan. The donation was intended as a gift as well as assistance in fighting the COVID-19 pandemic. The donation was jointly organized by the Chinese Embassy in Mauritania along with the 32 Chinese-funded enterprises and institutions. The exact agencies involved are unknown, as well as the contents of the medical donation and the value of the donation.

title: China’s Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region donates 30,000 surgical masks to the Association of Graduates from China in Mauritania and Chinguetti City
description: On June 24, 2020, the Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region announced a donation of 30,000 disposable medical masks to Mauritania. This donation was in response to the Covid-19 pandemic, and was given to the Association of Graduates from China in Mauritania and to Chinguetti City.   The supplies were shipped to Beijing before they arrived in Mauritania in August of 2020. The handover ceremonies for the donation were held on August 10 and 14, though it is unclear which recipient's ceremony came first.
staff_comments: AidData has estimated the transaction amount for this donation based on price catalogues from the World Health Organization (WHO). Please see the TUFF Methodology for additional details.
